# Testing Rules — Discursive

Tests run on both macOS (development) and Linux (CI). Write tests that pass on
both without conditional paths.

## Problem Classes

### `Tests with t.Setenv("HOME") use hardcoded platform paths`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Tests pass on macOS but fail on Linux CI: config written to XDG path (`~/.local/share/Discursive`) but test loads from hardcoded macOS path (`~/Library/Application Support/Discursive`) | Tests set `HOME` via `t.Setenv` but construct `dataRoot` with `filepath.Join(home, "Library", "Application Support", ...)` instead of the app's own cross-platform resolver | Use `config.DataRoot(config.ResolveOpts{Home: home})` to resolve the data root; never hardcode OS-specific data directories in tests |

### `CI vs local test divergence`

| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
| ----- | ---- | ----- |
| Tests pass locally (`go test`) but fail in CI with no obvious code change | OS-dependent paths, runtime.GOOS assumptions, or missing `GOFLAGS` for tag-filtered tests | Run `GOFLAGS="-tags=!live" go test ./...` to match CI; verify `config.DataRoot()` usage in all tests that set `HOME` |

